note:
alternates:

SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN member_id IS NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) 
FROM my_table;
or

SELECT SUM(member_id IS NULL)
FROM my_table;

For a schema/database in Databricks SQL, these are effectively similar terms:

DROP DATABASE customers CASCADE;
or:

DROP SCHEMA customers CASCADE;
CASCADE drops the schema/database and the objects inside it, such as tables and views.

For a table, use:

DROP TABLE table_name;
or with schema qualification:

DROP TABLE customers.orders;
There is no CASCADE needed for a normal table drop. A table is already the object being dropped.

Common related commands:

DROP VIEW view_name;
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS customers.orders;
DROP SCHEMA IF EXISTS customers CASCADE;
Important distinction:

DROP SCHEMA ... CASCADE drops the schema and its contained objects
DROP TABLE ... drops one table
For a managed table, Databricks also removes the managed table data
For an external table, Databricks removes the table metadata, but not the underlying data files
